Key Match Events: Saud Shakeel scored 68 runs off 52 balls, including nine boundaries and a six.
Pakistan beat Netherlands by 81 runs at the Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium in Hyderabad.
Shakeel formed a crucial 120-run partnership with Mohammad Rizwan.
Pakistan were reeling at 38 for 3 before Shakeel's partnership with Rizwan lifted them to a comfortable position.
Post-Match Reflections: Saud Shakeel expressed gratitude towards the coaching staff and the crowd for their support.
Shakeel dedicated his award to his coach.
Shakeel mentioned that he developed his game according to the team's needs and worked hard on his game in the last 2-3 months.
